{The best square for the Bishop.} (3. Bb5+ {is a check, but this loses time as 
Black can block and attack the Bishop.} 3... c6 {The Pawn is good here anyway, 
covering some key central squares.} 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. d3 Be7 {Black is comfortable 
and can expand in the centre with ...d5 in a few moves.}) (3. Bd3 {is poor, 
blocking in the Queen's Pawn and therefore the other Bishop.}) (3. Be2 {is a bit 
too passive.}) (3. Ba6 {is the worst possible move!} 3... Nxa6) *

