1. e4 d5 {The Scandinavian Defence. An interesting line where Black has to play 
accurately as he is potentially wasting a lot of time moving the Queen about.} 
2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 {The most natural and best move, developing a piece and 
attacking the Queen.} Qc6 {A really terrible blunder! Black has three moves 
which are all considered quite playable by modern opening theory:} (3... Qa5) 
(3... Qd6) ({and} 3... Qd8) 4. Bb5 {[%cal Gb5e8][%csl Rc6] Oh dear - the Bishop 
pins the Queen to the King and White is about to win lots of material.} *

