{The following game was played in Germany in 1940.} 1. e4 e5 2. f4 d5 3. Nf3 
dxe4 4. Nxe5 Nc6 5. Bb5 Nf6 {Black sets a little trap.} 6. Nxc6 {Not the best.} 
(6. Qe2 {was the best move with dangerous attacking potential.}) bxc6 7. Bxc6+ 
Bd7 8. Bxa8 {A mistake. Perhaps White had overlooked Black's idea.} (8. Bxd7+ 
Qxd7 {White has won a Pawn but Black has the easier game as White hasn't 
developed any queenside pieces and the Pawn on f4 means the white King is a 
little exposed even after castling. The game might continue as follows:} 9. O-O 
Bc5+ 10. Kh1 O-O 11. Nc3 Rad8 {with a tough battle ahead.}) Bg4 {[%cal 
Gg4d1][%csl Rd1] Black traps the white Queen!} *

