7. Qxf7# *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Mixed Opening Puzzles"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291226"]

{The main aim of the opening is to get a 'playable position'. Get your pieces 
out, take some control of the centre and make sure your King is safe. After 
this, the game truly begins. However, we must be alert. Our opponent may try to 
trap or trick us. Or, our opponents may make mistakes and gift us a golden 
opportunity to win the game early. Do not waste these chances! So try and follow 
the Four Opening Laws and avoid the Deadly Sins. However, if you calculate that 
a move is good, don't be afraid to go for it! Good luck!} 1. -- *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #1"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291213"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 Bb4+ {Play the best move.} 5. c3 {This is 
best - the pawn is well placed on c3 supporting an eventual d4 and White gains 
time by attacking the Bishop.} *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #2"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291214"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 c5 5. c3 Nc6 6. Nbd2 a6 {Play the best 
move.} 7. Bd3 {White develops the remaining minor piece to an active square.} 
(7. Be2 {is less active.}) Be7 8. O-O {White castles to safety.} *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #3"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291215"]

1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3 d6 4. Nf3 Be7 5. d3 O-O {Play the best move.} 6. Bg2 
{White continues with developing the pieces and prepares to castle.} (6. Bg5 {is 
OK, but it is better to prepare castling.}) Nbd7 7. O-O *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #4"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291216"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 d6 4. Nc3 Nge7 {Find the best move for White.} 5. Ng5 
{[%cal Gg5f7] Black cannot defend f7. Normally you shouldn't move the same piece 
twice in the opening but you absolutely should if you can exploit a weakness in 
the opponent's position (Opening Law 4).} h6 6. Nxf7 Qd7 7. Nxh8 *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #5"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291217"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 Bf5 3. cxd5 Qxd5 {Play the best move.} 4. Nc3 {White develops a 
piece and attacks the Queen.} Qd8 5. e4 {[%cal Gf1c4][%csl Ge4,Gd4] Grabbing the 
centre and enabling the Bishop to develop. White has a much better position.} *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #6"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291218"]

1. e4 d6 {Play the best move.} 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 {Developing a piece and 
protecting the Pawn on e4.} (3. Bd3 {is an OK move, though not as accurate as 
Nc3. In general we normally develop Knights before Bishops.}) *

[Event "Tournament Ready: The Opening"]
[Site "Final Test"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "14 - Exercise #7"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "15 Final Test"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "tournament-ready-the-opening/course/33414, variation/6291227"]

1. e4 d5 2. Nc3 d4 3. Nd5 e6 4. Nf4 {The only safe retreat square.} (4. Nb4 
Bxb4) *

